cashAccount.Tenx's Goals Account is a second (option: Tenx's Goals Account is a second (optional) account that you can open in addition to your Cash Account. A Stuff Account allows you to set aside money that you need in the short-term for things like rent, utilities, etc. The Stuff Account is similar to the Cash Account, but it does not have a debit card linked to it. It acts as a buffer that sets aside money that you know you need to spend soon, so you don't come up short when you need it. In order to use the money in the Stuff Account, you will need to transfer it to your Cash Account, which can be done in real-time using Tenx's webiste or from within the Tenx mobile app.
cashAccount.Tenx's Needs Account is a savings accoun: Tenx's Needs Account is a savings account that can be added if you have a Cash Account. It gives you another safe place to keep money you want to put away to spend on things further in the future. You can easily set savings goals and track your progress.

tenxPayEnroll.Things to Know about Tenx Pay: Things to Know about Tenx Pay
Tenx Pay is not a loan; it is not an extension of credit, and there is no payback period.
Hour and wage information is provided by your employer; you can access the money you've earned by initiating a request from within the Tenx app.
You can get your money within minutes, and will see the deduction on your next pay stub.
You can make up to 4 requests per pay period. An “Early Access Fee” will apply each time you request an expedited payment of the available money you've earned. The fee will be $3.00 per transaction, unless your employer has contracted otherwise. The fee will be displayed for you to review before you submit your request.
The fee is paid as part of the Tenx Pay transaction. The amount you receive will be the amount you requested less the fee amount.
For example: if you request $50, and there is a $3 fee, the $50 will be shown as a deduction on your next paycheck, and $47 will be sent to the account you selected.
As a reminder, the Early Access Fee applies each time you use the Tenx Pay service to receive a requested amount, unless noted as a free request on the confirmation screen.
